Dear Chairman Nenema:

This is in response to your letter of March 21, 2011, requesting this office to clarify Amendment 

III to the Constitution and Bylaws of the Kalispel Indian Community of the Kalispel Reservation. 

Kalispel Resolution No. 14 was enacted on July 30, 1975, by the Kalispel Business Committee to 

use the blood degrees as shown on the Basic Membership Roll of April 1, 1934, as all Kalispel 

Indian blood. It was the intent of the resolution to amend only Section 1 of Article II - 

Membership. Therefore the Amendment III should not have used the word "entirety" in 

amending Article II as it was only intended to amend Section 1. Section 2 of Article II shall 

remain the same and in effect as written. We hope this clarification will be of some assistance 

to the Tribe and its membership. If you have any questions, please contact Betty Scissons, 

Tribal Government Specialist, at (503) 231-6723.

Sincerely,

APR 06 2011

United States Department of the Interior
 
 
