Dear Chairman Nenema:

On August 29, 2019 we received Kalispel Resolution 2019-51 officially requesting a Secretarial 
election to decide one proposed amendment to the Revised Constitution and Bylaws of the Kalispel 
Indian Community of the Kalispel Reservation; to remove the Secretarial approval requirement from 
Article VII - Amendments.

The election was held on November 8, 2019. 25 CFR Parts 81.44 (a) through (f) require the Election 
Board Chair to transmit the following documents to the Authorizing Official: (a) the original text of 
the material voted on, (b) the Eligible Voters List, (c) the Registered Voters List, (d) the Secretarial 
Election Notice Packet, (e) any challenges to the Secretarial election results, and (f) the Certificate of 
Results of Election. After the mandatory five-day challenge period expired (25 CFR Part 81.43), the 
documents were transmitted as required. The Election Board advises there were no challenges.

A total of 58 eligible Kalispel tribal members registered to vote in this election. For the election to be 
valid at least 30 percent (17 people) of those registered must cast their ballots. The proposed ballot 
measure had 31 valid votes either for or against, making the election valid. 25 CFR 81.44(b)(1). The 
ballot measure was approved by the voters as noted in the Enclosed Certificate. 25 CFR 81.44(b)(2). 
The proposed amendments were reviewed prior to the election and were determined to not be 
contrary to Federal law. 25 CFR 81.44 (b)(3).

The Secretarial Election Board is to be commended for its efforts in this election. This constitutes a 
final agency action for the Bureau of Indian Affairs.

If you have further questions, please contact Greg Norton, Tribal Government Specialist, at 
(503)231-6723.

Sincerely,
 
  
  
  
 

