AMENDMENT IV:

Article VII of the Constitution, Amendments, shall be amended in its entirety to read as follows:

Article VII

Amendments

This revised constitution and bylaws may be amended by a majority vote of the qualified voters of the 
Kalispel Indian Community voting at an election called for that purpose by the Business Committee, 
provided that at least thirty (30) percent of eligible voters cast ballots.

It shall be the duty of the Business Committee to call an election on any proposed amendment upon 
being instructed to do so by a majority vote of either the Community Council or the Business Committee 
or upon the receipt of a petition for such signed by twenty-five (25) of the eligible voters of the Tribe.
 
 

CERTIFICATION OF RESULTS OF ELECTION

 
 Pursuant to a Secretarial Election authorized by the Northwest Regional Director on

August 29, 2019, the amendment to the Constitution of the Kalispel Indian Community of the

Kalispel Reservation was submitted to the qualified voters of the Kalispel Indian Community

on November 8, 2019. Proposed Amendment A was dull approved by a vote of 

29 for and 4 against, and 0 cast ballots found to be spoiled or mutilated in an

election in which 2/3 of the voting membership must be in favor of the amendment and at least 

thirty percent (30%) of the 58 members entitled to vote (registered to vote), cast their ballots. 

This Secretarial Election was conducted in accordance with Article III, Section 1 of the Tribal

Constitution and Bylaws.

Dated 11.8.2019
 
 

APPROVAL

 
 Bodie Shaw  ACTING

